1
00:00:09,233 --> 00:00:11,733
<i> Let me make it up to you</i>

2
00:00:11,867 --> 00:00:13,467
<i> for our fight last time.</i>

3
00:00:15,433 --> 00:00:17,200
<i> Paolo! Paolo!</i>

4
00:00:17,333 --> 00:00:18,500
<i>- Paolo!
- What?</i>

5
00:00:18,633 --> 00:00:19,600
<i>You're like a different person.</i>

6
00:00:19,733 --> 00:00:21,067
<i> You're hurting me.</i>

7
00:00:21,200 --> 00:00:22,067
<i> Just go to sleep.</i>

8
00:00:22,200 --> 00:00:23,500
<i>He seemed different last night.</i>

9
00:00:23,633 --> 00:00:26,267
<i>Maybe your husband just wants
to try something new?</i>

10
00:00:26,400 --> 00:00:27,400
<i> What's the game plan?</i>

11
00:00:27,533 --> 00:00:30,100
<i>I want to stay one step ahead
of your brother.</i>

12
00:00:30,233 --> 00:00:32,767
<i>I need to know everything
he's planning.</i>

13
00:00:32,900 --> 00:00:34,667
<i>- Edward?
- Oh, Lalaine.</i>

14
00:00:34,833 --> 00:00:37,933
<i>Tell your wife to at least
check in with me.</i>

15
00:00:38,067 --> 00:00:39,100
<i>- Hello?
- Hon, where are you?</i>

16
00:00:39,233 --> 00:00:40,667
<i> With Lalaine and the girls.</i>

17
00:00:40,800 --> 00:00:43,533
<i>- Are you sure?
- Yes, we're at the spa.</i>

18
00:00:43,667 --> 00:00:44,633
<i> What's your problem?</i>

19
00:00:44,767 --> 00:00:46,300
<i>Why do you have
to lie to me, huh?</i>

20
00:00:46,433 --> 00:00:48,367
<i>Where were you?
Who were you with?</i>

21
00:00:48,500 --> 00:00:50,667
<i>- Evelyn!
- What are you doing here?</i>

22
00:00:50,800 --> 00:00:53,267
<i>Can you just find someone else
to bother?</i>

23
00:00:53,400 --> 00:00:54,267
<i> Wow, you've got some nerve!</i>

24
00:00:54,400 --> 00:00:55,533
<i>- Go!
- Get out of here!</i>

25
00:00:55,667 --> 00:00:56,900
<i> We're not done yet!</i>

26
00:00:57,033 --> 00:00:58,300
<i> Are you okay?</i>

27
00:01:02,933 --> 00:01:04,167
Just breathe.

28
00:01:15,400 --> 00:01:17,000
I'm sorry, Greg.

29
00:01:18,433 --> 00:01:19,900
You were right...

30
00:01:20,733 --> 00:01:22,467
to kick that jerk out.

31
00:01:22,600 --> 00:01:24,133
Greg, I don't know why

32
00:01:24,267 --> 00:01:28,533
I'm like a magnet for losers.

33
00:01:29,400 --> 00:01:31,567
My first husband was a cheater.

34
00:01:32,300 --> 00:01:35,500
And now this guy
who's courting me?

35
00:01:35,633 --> 00:01:36,600
A drunkard.

36
00:01:38,300 --> 00:01:40,100
Just some bum hanging around
the streets.

37
00:01:43,900 --> 00:01:46,867
Don't waste your time on guys
like that.

38
00:01:47,500 --> 00:01:53,067
It's not just losers
who can fall for you.

39
00:02:01,467 --> 00:02:04,300
You deserve someone better,
Evelyn.

40
00:02:15,400 --> 00:02:17,000
Greg, I'll get going.

41
00:02:18,467 --> 00:02:21,100
Thanks for earlier.

42
00:03:15,467 --> 00:03:17,667
Love, I already picked out
your outfit today.

43
00:03:21,667 --> 00:03:24,067
Ah, I'll wear something else.

44
00:03:39,033 --> 00:03:42,800
Paolo, are we okay?

45
00:03:43,767 --> 00:03:45,033
What do you mean?

46
00:03:46,200 --> 00:03:48,100
I'm not picking a fight.

47
00:03:48,467 --> 00:03:49,967
I just want to understand.

48
00:03:50,867 --> 00:03:53,800
Even when we're together,
it feels like...

49
00:03:53,967 --> 00:03:55,833
like you've been distant lately.

50
00:03:55,967 --> 00:03:57,433
There's no issue.

51
00:03:57,567 --> 00:04:00,300
Maybe we're just in different
headspaces right now.

52
00:04:01,200 --> 00:04:05,100
And you know, I'm busy
on the Menagerie Manor.

53
00:04:05,233 --> 00:04:07,533
And you've got Jasmine's
treatment, right?

54
00:04:12,533 --> 00:04:14,333
I feel like there's...

55
00:04:14,467 --> 00:04:16,333
something else.

56
00:04:16,467 --> 00:04:17,900
Something changed.

57
00:04:21,900 --> 00:04:24,767
Did I say something wrong
when we made up?

58
00:04:26,933 --> 00:04:28,567
Did I do something?

59
00:04:30,100 --> 00:04:32,633
If something happened,
just tell me.

60
00:04:32,767 --> 00:04:34,267
Is there a problem?

61
00:04:34,400 --> 00:04:36,633
You won't even talk to me.

62
00:04:38,100 --> 00:04:40,400
Are you hiding something
from me?

63
00:05:00,233 --> 00:05:01,300
Marj.

64
00:05:03,233 --> 00:05:07,433
Marj, you're probably just
overthinking.

65
00:05:07,567 --> 00:05:09,333
Love, I'm not imagining this.

66
00:05:09,467 --> 00:05:11,000
This is how I feel.

67
00:05:11,133 --> 00:05:12,467
But that doesn't mean

68
00:05:12,600 --> 00:05:14,467
I'm hiding anything from you.

69
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:19,933
What do you want me to do?
What do you want to happen?

70
00:05:20,067 --> 00:05:21,433
Every time I go quiet,

71
00:05:21,567 --> 00:05:23,100
I need to explain myself...

72
00:05:24,233 --> 00:05:26,167
just so you won't overthink?

73
00:05:27,100 --> 00:05:29,567
That's not what I meant.

74
00:05:30,033 --> 00:05:32,300
I just want us to go back
to how we were.

75
00:05:32,433 --> 00:05:33,733
Marj...

76
00:05:37,300 --> 00:05:39,467
Things have changed.

77
00:05:40,067 --> 00:05:42,600
Jasmine's going through
something.

78
00:05:42,733 --> 00:05:45,367
There are problems
at the company.

79
00:05:45,500 --> 00:05:49,600
Can we just use whatever energy
we have left on those things...

80
00:05:50,700 --> 00:05:54,033
instead of this?

81
00:06:11,867 --> 00:06:13,667
Oscar!

82
00:06:30,033 --> 00:06:31,567
Marj.

83
00:06:33,267 --> 00:06:36,300
Is this still about you
and Paolo?

84
00:06:39,033 --> 00:06:41,067
It's nothing, Mom,
I'm just tired.

85
00:06:42,700 --> 00:06:46,100
Marj, don't lie to me.

86
00:06:46,633 --> 00:06:49,167
Nothing gets past me
in this house.

87
00:06:50,567 --> 00:06:54,900
Even the maids notice your
husband coming home late

88
00:06:55,033 --> 00:06:57,467
and leaving early.

89
00:06:58,300 --> 00:07:00,233
I know my son.

90
00:07:00,867 --> 00:07:04,033
And I know what a woman looks
like when she's pretending

91
00:07:04,167 --> 00:07:06,367
to be okay, but isn't.

92
00:07:07,233 --> 00:07:08,600
Listen.

93
00:07:08,733 --> 00:07:10,467
Crying in the garden?

94
00:07:10,600 --> 00:07:12,067
Very dramatic.

95
00:07:12,200 --> 00:07:14,567
But unnecessary.

96
00:07:14,733 --> 00:07:16,100
That's not a solution.

97
00:07:16,900 --> 00:07:19,300
If there's a problem,
do something.

98
00:07:19,433 --> 00:07:22,267
Don't stop trying to win
your husband back.

99
00:07:24,333 --> 00:07:26,033
I am trying.

100
00:07:26,167 --> 00:07:28,233
Then try harder.

101
00:07:29,433 --> 00:07:30,933
Are you okay?

102
00:07:31,067 --> 00:07:32,600
Let's just get through this day.

103
00:07:34,267 --> 00:07:36,133
This is about Marj, right?

104
00:07:37,400 --> 00:07:40,267
Thea, please, you don't need
to check in on me like that.

105
00:07:41,500 --> 00:07:44,333
It should be clear to you
what we are.

106
00:07:44,467 --> 00:07:47,600
And you're not my BFF to share

107
00:07:47,767 --> 00:07:49,067
my personal problems.

108
00:07:50,233 --> 00:07:51,433
What we have...

109
00:07:52,900 --> 00:07:54,000
work...

110
00:07:54,133 --> 00:07:55,433
stays in the office.

111
00:07:56,467 --> 00:07:58,433
And the other,

112
00:07:58,567 --> 00:07:59,933
stays in bed.

113
00:08:01,767 --> 00:08:09,633
Or wherever you need
your release.

114
00:08:11,267 --> 00:08:13,400
Men like Paolo

115
00:08:13,533 --> 00:08:14,800
and his father

116
00:08:14,933 --> 00:08:18,300
don't tell you
when they're pulling away.

117
00:08:18,433 --> 00:08:21,333
When they don't get
the attention they want

118
00:08:21,500 --> 00:08:23,167
from their wives,

119
00:08:23,300 --> 00:08:26,167
that's when they start
looking elsewhere.

120
00:08:27,267 --> 00:08:29,867
You don't want
to wake up one day

121
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:32,367
and realize your husband
has no more love for you

122
00:08:32,500 --> 00:08:34,800
and is looking for it
somewhere else.

123
00:08:37,533 --> 00:08:39,867
The Torrecampo wife

124
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:42,867
knows how to keep
her marriage intact.

125
00:08:43,533 --> 00:08:48,300
With grace, with effort,
with presence.

126
00:08:48,933 --> 00:08:51,667
Even when it hurts,
even when it's hard...

127
00:08:52,567 --> 00:08:54,767
act like a Torrecampo woman.

128
00:08:55,700 --> 00:08:57,933
It's not too late.

129
00:08:58,067 --> 00:09:00,500
But it is a choice.

130
00:09:16,900 --> 00:09:17,867
Thank you, Mr. Santos,

131
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:20,433
for agreeing to meet with us
today.

132
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:23,767
I know you're busy,

133
00:09:23,900 --> 00:09:27,567
but all the files
you requested are there.

134
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:29,400
Okay, feel free to go through it

135
00:09:29,533 --> 00:09:34,400
and then if you have any
questions, please ask.

136
00:09:39,367 --> 00:09:40,133
Everything's there,

137
00:09:40,267 --> 00:09:42,200
all the clauses
we discussed before.

138
00:09:42,333 --> 00:09:45,433
Everything's complete, right?

139
00:09:47,100 --> 00:09:48,100
Wow!

140
00:09:48,633 --> 00:09:50,633
He's really rubbing it in.

141
00:09:52,633 --> 00:09:54,700
Paolo, we can't let Aldrin
get ahead of us

142
00:09:54,833 --> 00:09:56,300
on Menagerie Manor.

143
00:09:56,433 --> 00:09:57,867
We can't let him win.

144
00:09:59,400 --> 00:10:00,733
He's not getting ahead of us.

145
00:10:01,800 --> 00:10:03,000
We'll stick to the plan.

146
00:10:03,633 --> 00:10:05,267
We just add urgency.

147
00:10:06,467 --> 00:10:07,567
Urgency?

148
00:10:08,067 --> 00:10:09,233
How?

149
00:10:09,367 --> 00:10:13,933
Making sure the right people
move before Aldrin can close.

150
00:10:32,500 --> 00:10:33,933
Thank you.

151
00:10:40,100 --> 00:10:42,367
Mom, you look extra
pretty today.

152
00:10:43,467 --> 00:10:45,467
- Really?
- Yes.

153
00:10:46,567 --> 00:10:48,600
But something's missing.

154
00:10:50,067 --> 00:10:52,667
Mom, can you hand something
in that drawer?

155
00:10:52,800 --> 00:10:55,167
There's a jewelry box in there.

156
00:11:02,200 --> 00:11:03,300
Thank you.

157
00:11:08,733 --> 00:11:09,667
Here, Mom.

158
00:11:09,800 --> 00:11:10,867
Wear this.

159
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:12,467
It matches your dress.

160
00:11:17,033 --> 00:11:18,500
Okay, let's see.

161
00:11:19,400 --> 00:11:20,700
Can I see?

162
00:11:25,333 --> 00:11:28,433
Wow, you really are
my stylist, huh?

163
00:11:30,733 --> 00:11:34,733
I hope your dad likes this
when I surprise him later.

164
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:38,333
Thank you.

165
00:11:42,700 --> 00:11:46,133
Mom, are you and Dad
still not okay

166
00:11:46,267 --> 00:11:48,267
since the Hong Kong treatment?

167
00:11:49,967 --> 00:11:51,867
Your dad and I will work
things out.

168
00:11:52,000 --> 00:11:53,733
Nothing to worry about.

169
00:11:55,733 --> 00:11:57,100
Sorry, Mom.

170
00:11:57,667 --> 00:12:00,667
I didn't mean to cause
all this mess by getting sick.

171
00:12:02,767 --> 00:12:05,333
Jasmine, listen to me.

172
00:12:06,833 --> 00:12:09,000
This isn't because of you, okay?

173
00:12:09,700 --> 00:12:11,467
This isn't about your illness.

174
00:12:12,667 --> 00:12:17,200
Your dad and I just have some
things to fix between us.

175
00:12:17,367 --> 00:12:19,267
And we'll be okay.

176
00:12:19,400 --> 00:12:20,633
This is not your fault.

177
00:12:21,300 --> 00:12:23,367
I just want things
to be better, Mom.

178
00:12:24,133 --> 00:12:27,533
Not just my health,
but our family, too.

179
00:12:28,833 --> 00:12:32,800
Because you, Dad,
and my friends...

180
00:12:32,933 --> 00:12:34,933
You're all I have to hold on to
right now.

181
00:12:36,133 --> 00:12:38,433
We'll be okay, sweetheart.

182
00:12:38,567 --> 00:12:40,167
And I promise you,

183
00:12:40,300 --> 00:12:43,633
I'll do everything to keep
our family strong.

184
00:12:44,467 --> 00:12:47,233
We love you so much, Jasmine.

185
00:12:47,367 --> 00:12:48,700
Your dad and I.

186
00:12:49,600 --> 00:12:51,467
I know, Mom.

187
00:12:51,600 --> 00:12:54,300
And I know that you and Dad
love each other so much.

188
00:12:54,433 --> 00:12:57,067
So you won't let this fight
go on any longer.

189
00:12:58,000 --> 00:12:59,533
I need both of you
in my fight, Mom,

190
00:12:59,667 --> 00:13:01,033
so I can get better.

191
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:03,400
Please.

192
00:13:19,433 --> 00:13:21,033
Sir, please don't
leave yet, okay?

193
00:13:21,667 --> 00:13:23,900
We have an important
announcement later.

194
00:13:24,033 --> 00:13:25,567
I'm sure you'll like it.

195
00:13:25,700 --> 00:13:27,500
- Okay.
- And, Sir,

196
00:13:27,633 --> 00:13:29,233
about Menagerie Manor,

197
00:13:29,367 --> 00:13:32,367
we only use the high quality
materials.

198
00:13:32,500 --> 00:13:33,500
Yes.

199
00:13:33,633 --> 00:13:35,200
You'll love it, It's close
to the hospital and...

200
00:13:35,933 --> 00:13:37,700
- Thank you, Sir.
- Thank you.

201
00:13:41,567 --> 00:13:42,767
So this is it.

202
00:13:43,633 --> 00:13:45,300
Another open house party.

203
00:13:47,033 --> 00:13:48,700
You spent all this money
on a place

204
00:13:48,833 --> 00:13:50,500
that still can't sell.

205
00:13:51,400 --> 00:13:53,467
Not a single unit.

206
00:13:53,600 --> 00:13:55,600
You're looking at it
the wrong way.

207
00:13:56,933 --> 00:13:58,333
This isn't an open house.

208
00:13:59,100 --> 00:14:00,367
It's a filter.

209
00:14:02,333 --> 00:14:04,267
Watch and learn.

210
00:14:06,167 --> 00:14:07,633
Good afternoon, everyone.

211
00:14:08,100 --> 00:14:09,467
Good afternoon.

212
00:14:09,600 --> 00:14:12,267
Thank you for taking the time
to be here.

213
00:14:14,800 --> 00:14:18,100
Menagerie Manor was never
designed for volume.

214
00:14:18,233 --> 00:14:21,333
It was designed
for the right owners.

215
00:14:21,833 --> 00:14:25,567
That said, the market today
rewards decisiveness.

216
00:14:26,333 --> 00:14:28,767
So we're making one more move.

217
00:14:29,900 --> 00:14:31,200
Clear.

218
00:14:32,100 --> 00:14:33,367
Time-bound.

219
00:14:35,700 --> 00:14:37,800
We're opening a flash sale
today.

220
00:14:37,933 --> 00:14:41,200
30 percent off for the first
unit secured today.

221
00:14:41,333 --> 00:14:43,767
Not reserved.

222
00:14:43,900 --> 00:14:45,000
Secured.

223
00:14:45,133 --> 00:14:46,767
30 percent?

224
00:14:46,900 --> 00:14:47,933
Today?

225
00:14:48,067 --> 00:14:50,133
Yes, today.

226
00:14:50,267 --> 00:14:53,167
After that, pricing goes back
to standard.

227
00:14:57,300 --> 00:14:59,933
And the availability
becomes limited.

228
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:04,133
This isn't about discount.

229
00:15:04,633 --> 00:15:06,433
It's about access.

230
00:15:06,567 --> 00:15:09,700
Now who's ready to move
in when it matters?

231
00:15:19,933 --> 00:15:21,733
Enjoy the win.

232
00:15:21,867 --> 00:15:25,000
Because this is where it starts
to cost you.

233
00:15:28,933 --> 00:15:30,433
I'm interested.

234
00:15:30,833 --> 00:15:32,633
Let's talk numbers.

235
00:15:34,800 --> 00:15:36,167
Of course.

236
00:15:39,200 --> 00:15:40,333
This way, Sir.

237
00:15:40,467 --> 00:15:41,433
Thank you.

238
00:16:02,633 --> 00:16:04,167
Everyone.

239
00:16:04,733 --> 00:16:10,200
Good work today.
Congratulations.

240
00:16:10,367 --> 00:16:11,967
- Gemma.
- Yes, Sir.

241
00:16:12,100 --> 00:16:12,900
You take care
of everything, okay?

242
00:16:13,033 --> 00:16:13,933
Please take charge.

243
00:16:14,067 --> 00:16:15,200
- Yes, Sir.
- Okay?

244
00:16:16,533 --> 00:16:17,667
Paolo.

245
00:16:19,033 --> 00:16:20,467
Congratulations.

246
00:16:20,600 --> 00:16:21,567
Thank you.

247
00:16:24,467 --> 00:16:27,200
I have your reward
waiting for you.

248
00:16:29,967 --> 00:16:32,833
Inside the shower of the
master's bedroom.

249
00:18:05,567 --> 00:18:08,133
Okay, make sure everything's
all set, all right?

250
00:18:08,267 --> 00:18:10,100
I'll go ahead.

251
00:18:10,233 --> 00:18:11,933
- Thank you.
- Okay.

252
00:18:12,067 --> 00:18:13,967
Hi, Ma'am Marj,
good evening.

253
00:18:14,100 --> 00:18:16,867
Hi, Gemma,
congrats on your open house.

254
00:18:17,000 --> 00:18:18,033
Thank you, Ma'am.

255
00:18:18,167 --> 00:18:20,000
Where's Paolo?

256
00:18:20,133 --> 00:18:22,100
He's probably upstairs.

257
00:18:22,500 --> 00:18:23,700
Okay,
I'll go check on him.

258
00:18:23,833 --> 00:18:25,700
- Thank you.
- Thanks.

259
00:18:32,700 --> 00:18:33,967
Love?

260
00:18:36,233 --> 00:18:37,300
Love?

261
00:18:46,767 --> 00:18:48,100
Love?

262
00:18:56,700 --> 00:18:57,933
Love?

263
00:19:36,567 --> 00:19:37,700
Love?

264
00:19:39,600 --> 00:19:40,733
Love?

265
00:19:42,000 --> 00:19:43,300
It's Marj!

266
00:20:38,700 --> 00:20:39,767
Oh, Love.

267
00:20:40,733 --> 00:20:41,933
What are you doing here?

268
00:20:43,667 --> 00:20:46,500
Ah, I wanted to surprise you.

269
00:20:46,633 --> 00:20:49,500
Didn't realize I'd be the one
getting surprised.

270
00:20:54,900 --> 00:20:57,300
It was really hot earlier,
so I just took a quick shower

271
00:20:57,433 --> 00:20:58,600
to cool off.

272
00:21:00,367 --> 00:21:01,967
You could've done that at home.

273
00:21:04,467 --> 00:21:08,867
Or maybe you didn't want to go
home because you're avoiding me?

274
00:21:09,033 --> 00:21:10,600
And why would you say that?

275
00:21:22,400 --> 00:21:26,167
Because even though you keep
telling me we're okay...

276
00:21:27,933 --> 00:21:30,267
I still feel like
you're upset with me.

277
00:21:31,400 --> 00:21:34,467
So I decided to come here
so we could talk...

278
00:21:35,333 --> 00:21:36,700
fix things.

279
00:21:37,733 --> 00:21:39,833
All right,
I'll just get dressed.

280
00:21:40,567 --> 00:21:41,767
Just wait for me downstairs.

281
00:21:43,733 --> 00:21:46,100
You always ruin
everything, Marj.

282
00:21:47,367 --> 00:21:49,167
It was supposed to be
a happy ending,

283
00:21:49,300 --> 00:21:51,233
and you still managed
to mess it up.

284
00:22:11,200 --> 00:22:13,367
Why did the staff
leave the door open?

285
00:22:17,067 --> 00:22:18,167
Marj!

286
00:22:22,933 --> 00:22:24,033
Wait!

287
00:22:25,400 --> 00:22:26,567
Marj! Marj, don't!

288
00:22:28,500 --> 00:22:30,167
Why? Is something wrong?

289
00:22:30,900 --> 00:22:32,300
Ah...

290
00:22:32,967 --> 00:22:34,067
I needed some air.

291
00:22:34,200 --> 00:22:35,300
I can't breathe here.

292
00:22:35,700 --> 00:22:37,933
Go ahead, head downstairs,
just wait for me there.

293
00:22:38,067 --> 00:22:39,133
Come on.

294
00:23:24,467 --> 00:23:25,800
Ah, Miss Marj, excuse us.

295
00:23:25,933 --> 00:23:27,100
We're heading out.

296
00:23:27,233 --> 00:23:28,967
- Sure, take care.
- Good night.

297
00:23:29,100 --> 00:23:30,500
Be safe, too.

298
00:23:48,533 --> 00:23:50,133
Love?

299
00:23:50,267 --> 00:23:51,600
Love?

300
00:23:51,733 --> 00:23:53,400
- Oh?
- Are you okay?

301
00:23:54,433 --> 00:23:56,600
You've been acting weird
since earlier.

302
00:23:57,367 --> 00:23:58,600
Yes... I'm just tired.

303
00:23:59,800 --> 00:24:00,767
Didn't I tell you,

304
00:24:00,900 --> 00:24:02,433
you didn't need to come here?

305
00:24:03,400 --> 00:24:04,400
You should've just stayed home

306
00:24:04,533 --> 00:24:05,800
and watched over Jasmine.

307
00:24:06,800 --> 00:24:10,000
Paolo, I just wanted you
to feel my support.

308
00:24:11,133 --> 00:24:12,533
I know you have problems

309
00:24:12,667 --> 00:24:14,300
and you're stressed
about the Menagerie project...

310
00:24:14,433 --> 00:24:17,700
and I don't want you
to feel that you're alone.

311
00:24:17,833 --> 00:24:19,133
That I'm here.

312
00:24:23,167 --> 00:24:24,600
I appreciate the support.

313
00:24:28,100 --> 00:24:29,500
But I can handle this.

314
00:24:35,833 --> 00:24:36,967
Okay.

315
00:24:38,233 --> 00:24:40,600
Let's just go home
so you can get some rest.

316
00:24:46,167 --> 00:24:47,700
Love?

317
00:24:47,833 --> 00:24:50,833
Next time, just tell me
if you're coming.

318
00:24:50,967 --> 00:24:54,333
What if we wrapped up early,
and I wasn't here?

319
00:24:55,267 --> 00:24:57,300
You would've just wasted
your time.

320
00:25:33,967 --> 00:25:35,433
I'm so sorry, Marj.

321
00:25:35,600 --> 00:25:38,033
Honestly, I feel bad for you.

322
00:25:38,167 --> 00:25:39,800
You need all the help
you can get.

323
00:25:39,933 --> 00:25:42,600
Bring Evelyn and Jobert back

324
00:25:42,733 --> 00:25:45,333
so they can help take care
of my grandchild.

325
00:25:45,467 --> 00:25:47,667
What?
I won't allow them to ruin

326
00:25:47,800 --> 00:25:49,867
the peace in my house.

327
00:25:50,000 --> 00:25:53,000
Keep an eye on Evelyn
and Jobert.

328
00:25:53,133 --> 00:25:56,567
We need to find something,
any dirt on them.

329
00:25:56,700 --> 00:25:59,067
So Greg will be forced
to kick them out.

330
00:26:00,100 --> 00:26:02,533
Ma'am Evelyn's up to something.

331
00:26:07,500 --> 00:26:09,767
We need to lie low
for a few days.

332
00:26:09,933 --> 00:26:12,700
We almost got caught
by Marj last time.

333
00:26:12,833 --> 00:26:16,633
I don't want her getting
suspicious or figuring us out.

334
00:26:16,767 --> 00:26:19,167
I was already left hanging
last time...

335
00:26:19,300 --> 00:26:21,500
and now you want to avoid me,
too?

336
00:26:21,633 --> 00:26:22,867
Okay, okay, fine.

337
00:26:23,000 --> 00:26:25,667
I'll book a hotel this Friday.

338
00:26:25,800 --> 00:26:27,900
Safer, no more surprises.

339
00:26:28,033 --> 00:26:29,833
Paolo's no longer at the office.

340
00:26:29,967 --> 00:26:31,667
He's at the Olympo Hotel.

341
00:26:31,800 --> 00:26:33,333
What's Paolo doing at a hotel?

342
00:26:33,467 --> 00:26:34,867
Hello, love?
Are you at the office?

343
00:26:35,000 --> 00:26:36,233
Yes, I'm at the office,
I'll just finish this up,

344
00:26:36,367 --> 00:26:37,500
then I'll call you back, okay?

345
00:26:37,633 --> 00:26:38,533
Okay, bye.

346
00:26:38,667 --> 00:26:40,633
Paolo lied to me.

347
00:26:40,767 --> 00:26:42,833
He told me he was just
at the office.

348
00:26:43,000 --> 00:26:44,233
It just feels off.

349
00:26:44,367 --> 00:26:46,500
Marj never asks where I am.

350
00:26:46,633 --> 00:26:48,533
What if she's starting
to get suspicious?
